<section id="how-to-make-better-presentations" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="how-to-make-better-presentations">How to make better presentations</h2>
<div id="fig-presentation-futurama" class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center quarto-float anchored" data-fig-align="center">
<figure class="quarto-float quarto-float-fig figure">
<div aria-describedby="fig-presentation-futurama-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
<img src="www/images/presentation-futurama.jpg" class="img-fluid quarto-figure quarto-figure-center figure-img">
</div>
<figcaption class="quarto-float-caption-bottom quarto-float-caption quarto-float-fig" id="fig-presentation-futurama-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
Figure&nbsp;17: Futurama Fry meme with the text, “Not sure if people say my presentation was good, because it is good or if they feel bad for me because it sucked.”
</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p>Many of the information and example slides provided here were created by my colleague, <a href="https://policyviz.com/about/">Jon Schwabish</a>, a senior fellow at the Urban Institute and an author of several books on data visualization and communication. I’ve also added a few personal tips.</p>
<section id="designing-your-presentation" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="designing-your-presentation">Designing your presentation</h3>
<ul>
<li>Don’t race to your computer</li>
<li>Outline, sketch (use post-its and index cards)</li>
</ul>
<div id="fig-better-presentation-20" class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center quarto-float anchored" data-fig-align="center">
<figure class="quarto-float quarto-float-fig figure">
<div aria-describedby="fig-better-presentation-20-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
<img src="www/images/better-presentations-20.png" class="img-fluid quarto-figure quarto-figure-center figure-img" style="width:80.0%">
</div>
<figcaption class="quarto-float-caption-bottom quarto-float-caption quarto-float-fig" id="fig-better-presentation-20-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
Figure&nbsp;18: Designing your presentation image from Jon Schwabish.
</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<section id="the-hourglass-structure" class="level4">
<h4 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="the-hourglass-structure">The Hourglass structure</h4>
<p>Typically, the presentation structure is as follows, resembling a pyramid in terms of content and time:</p>
<ol type="1">
<li>Introduction</li>
<li>Previous literature</li>
<li>Data</li>
<li>Methods</li>
<li>Results</li>
<li>Conclusions</li>
</ol>
<p>However, it should be more like an hourglass. You want to spend more time getting people hooked at the beginning and then dedicate more time on the conclusions and takeaway at the end.</p>
<div id="fig-better-presentation-25" class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center quarto-float anchored" data-fig-align="center">
<figure class="quarto-float quarto-float-fig figure">
<div aria-describedby="fig-better-presentation-25-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
<img src="www/images/better-presentations-25.png" class="img-fluid quarto-figure quarto-figure-center figure-img" style="width:80.0%">
</div>
<figcaption class="quarto-float-caption-bottom quarto-float-caption quarto-float-fig" id="fig-better-presentation-25-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
Figure&nbsp;19: Hourglass presentation structure.
</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
</section>
<section id="presentation-worksheet" class="level4">
<h4 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="presentation-worksheet">Presentation worksheet</h4>
<p>The <a href="https://policyviz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Better_Presentations_Worksheet.pdf">presentation worksheet</a> helps you organize your presentation. It involves the following:</p>
<ol type="1">
<li>What types of presentation are you giving?</li>
<li>Who is your audience?</li>
<li>What is the headline message of your presentation?</li>
<li>What do you want your audience to do with your conclusions?</li>
<li>Craft your opening statement.</li>
<li>Craft your closing statement</li>
<li>Outline the sections of your presentation.</li>
<li>What stories can you tell?</li>
<li>Images (sketch or describe before searching).</li>
<li>Anticipated Q&amp;A.</li>
</ol>
</section>
<section id="resources" class="level4">
<h4 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="resources">Resources</h4>
<p>Jon provided <a href="https://policyviz.com/books/better-presentations/book-materials/">materials</a> that he mentions in his book, “<a href="https://policyviz.com/books/">Better Presentations: A Guide for Scholars, Researchers, and Wonks</a>” for free on his website. The materials include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Better Presentations Supplies Checklist</li>
<li>Better Presentations Worksheet</li>
<li>Color Palettes</li>
<li>Grids</li>
<li>Header Slides</li>
<li>Icons</li>
<li>Title Slides</li>
<li>References</li>
</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section id="building-your-presentation" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="building-your-presentation">Building your presentation</h3>
<div id="fig-powerpoint" class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center quarto-float anchored" data-fig-align="center">
<figure class="quarto-float quarto-float-fig figure">
<div aria-describedby="fig-powerpoint-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
<img src="www/images/powerpoint.gif" class="img-fluid quarto-figure quarto-figure-center figure-img">
</div>
<figcaption class="quarto-float-caption-bottom quarto-float-caption quarto-float-fig" id="fig-powerpoint-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
Figure&nbsp;20: Michael Scott, from the TV series, “The Office,” saying, “Powerpoint. Powerpoint. Powerpoint.”
</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<section id="text-slides" class="level4">
<h4 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="text-slides">Text slides</h4>
<ul>
<li>Slides are not a document</li>
<li>Slides are free</li>
<li>Layer your slides</li>
<li>“The more visual the input becomes, the more likely it is to be recognized and recalled.” John Medina, <em>Brian Rules</em>.</li>
<li>Slides should be visual</li>
<li>Spell check and copyedit</li>
</ul>
