<section id="communication-collaboration-and-culture" class="level1">
<h1>Communication, Collaboration, and Culture</h1>
<p>The following are questions I received from students in our first class.</p>
<section id="collaboration" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="collaboration">Collaboration</h2>
<section id="slack-teams-discord-oh-my-how-and-when-to-use-other-communication-platforms" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="slack-teams-discord-oh-my-how-and-when-to-use-other-communication-platforms">Slack, Teams, Discord, oh my! How and when to use other communication platforms?</h3>
<div id="fig-tools" class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center quarto-float anchored" data-fig-align="center">
<figure class="quarto-float quarto-float-fig figure">
<div aria-describedby="fig-tools-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
<img src="www/images/tools-futurama.jpg" class="img-fluid quarto-figure quarto-figure-center figure-img">
</div>
<figcaption class="quarto-float-caption-bottom quarto-float-caption quarto-float-fig" id="fig-tools-caption-0ceaefa1-69ba-4598-a22c-09a6ac19f8ca">
Figure&nbsp;49: Futurama Fry meme with the text, “Not sure if these tools suck or I don’t know how they work.”
</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p>I use messaging platforms like Slack, Teams, and Discord (yes, I use all three) for real-time messaging and file sharing. They help organize informal conversations through threads and manage projects effectively. Some examples of how I use these platforms include channels for:</p>
<ul>
<li>subteams</li>
<li>individual projects</li>
<li>common interests on a topic or tool</li>
<li>social (e.g., cats, great outdoors)</li>
</ul>
<div id="fig-urban-slack" class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center quarto-float anchored" data-fig-align="center">
<figure class="quarto-float quarto-float-fig figure">
